'''''Northern Fleet''''' is a 1988 video game published by [[Simulations Canada]].

==Gameplay==
''Northern Fleet'' is a game in which operations for the American or Soviet naval forces in the [[North Atlantic]] are simulated.<ref name="CGW62"/>

==Reception==
M. Evan Brooks reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "In ''Northern Fleet'', much of what is happening is hidden behind the immutable source code of the computer. Nevertheless, it is a clear success as it presents the "appearance" of historical accuracy."<ref name="CGW62">{{cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |title=Testing the Maritime Strategy: SimCan's "Northern Fleet" |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=August 1989 |volume=1 |issue=62 |pages=29â€“30}}</ref>

